h4 #{Constants[Enums.Positions.STRIKER]} or #{Constants[Enums.Positions.JACK]} only
p
    | Only a player with the  
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Abilities.JUMP}") #{Constants[Enums.Abilities.JUMP]} 
    | ability may perform a #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} action.
p
    | #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} is part of a 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.RUN}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.RUN]} 
    | or 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.SPRINT}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SPRINT]} 
    | action that allows the player to leap over teammates or opponents. It is a 
    | 2 hex move (and costs 2 hexes of movement).

h5 #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} is a 3 dice Speed test (123)
ul
    li +1 if the player is a #{Constants[Enums.Positions.STRIKER]}.
    li
        | -1 per opposing player threatening the hex the player is moving
        strong from
        | (maximum of -2).

table.table.table-striped
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} fails
        td
            | The player falls over into the target hex. If a loose ball was in 
            | the target hex, then the ball scatters and the rush continues normally. 
            | If the player was carrying the ball, then the ball scatters 
            | and the rush ends.
    tr
        td #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} succeeds
        td
            | The player moves into the target hex and may face any direction (even 
            | if the action was taken during a #{Constants[Enums.Actions.SPRINT]}. 
            | The player may make another #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} attempt 
            | with +1 to the target number of successes.

p
    | Note that a player falling over as part of a failed #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} 
    | does not have to make an #{Constants[Enums.Actions.ARMOR_CHECK]} and will not 
    | be injured. However, if they are carrying the ball then the ball will scatter 
    | and end the rush.
p
    | Also note that a player may need to 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.DASH}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DASH]} 
    | in order to gain the extra movement to #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} into 
    | a new hex. Roll each test separately. If the player fails any #{Constants[Enums.Actions.DASH]} 
    | attempts that are required for the #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} then they 
    | will fall over into the hex they were attempting to #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} 
    | into.
p
    | A player making a #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} does not need to roll an 
    a(href="/actions/#{Enums.Actions.EVADE}") #{Constants[Enums.Actions.EVADE]} 
    | for that part of their movement, though they are subject to the normal rules 
    | both before and after the #{Constants[Enums.Actions.JUMP]} attempt.
